edu.uw.cs.cse461.util

Class IPFinder.IPChooser

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uw.cs.cse461.util.IPFinder.IPChooser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPFinder.NetworkInterfaceCallbackInterface
    Enclosing class:
    IPFinder

    private static class IPFinder.IPChooser
extends Object
implements IPFinder.NetworkInterfaceCallbackInterface
    This class uses the interface iterator method below to apply a heuristic that tries to identify "the IP" for the machine we're running on. The rules for that are:
    • We consider only the available IPv4 addresses as candidates.
    • We prefer globally routable addresses to non-routable addresses.
    If this results in a single IP address, we select it as "the IP." If we end up with more than one, some external code must select one before we can answer calls to return "the IP." (In our projects, the user is asked.)
    Author:
    zahorjan
